## Cohort designer — dependent shared-class / via dropdowns

Context: In the cohort rule designer's *"When are two members linked?"*
section, the `share a <class> via <predicate>` row showed every ontology
class and every object property regardless of whether the predicate
actually connected the source class to the chosen shared class. Users
could pick incoherent combinations like *"Person — assignedTo — Office"*
that would silently produce zero edges at preview time.

The dropdowns are now dependent: the `via` selector is disabled until a
shared class is picked, and is then narrowed to object properties whose
`domain` is the source class and `range` is the picked shared class.
The `shared a` selector is itself narrowed to classes reachable from the
source class. If the ontology has incomplete domain/range metadata the
filters fall back to the broader list so the user is never locked out.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - Added `_classNameByUri`, `_objectPropsForSource`,
     `_compatibleSharedClasses`, `_compatibleViaProperties` helpers
     (class-name / URI / domain / range bridging — properties carry
     `domain`/`range` as class names per `Ontology.build_property`).
   - `_renderLinks()` now consumes those helpers: shared-class options
     are restricted to reachable ranges; via options are restricted to
     properties matching `domain=source` AND `range=shared_class`.
   - Selecting a different `shared_class` clears any stale `via` that no
     longer matches and re-renders the row in place.
   - Source-class change (`#cohortClassUri.onchange`) now also re-renders
     the link rows so both filters refresh together.
   - Disabled-state placeholder text on `via` ("pick a class first" /
     "no compatible relationship") makes the dependency obvious.

2. releasereq/cohort_design.md
   - §6.3 expanded with an explicit "Dependent dropdowns" paragraph
     documenting the `domain`/`range` filtering and the disabled state.

3. docs/cohort_discovery.md
   - §2 step 3 ("When are two members linked?") rewritten to describe
     the dependent dropdowns and the disabled-until-class-picked rule.

