## Cohort designer — multi-hop linkage paths

Context: The "When are two members linked?" section only supported
single-hop togetherness predicates of the form
`<source> —via→ <shared_class>`. To express *"two persons are linked
when they work on projects governed by the same compliance type"* a
user previously had to materialise a synthetic predicate
(`:hasCompliance` on `:Person`) just to bridge the two real edges. Each
link row was rigidly source-anchored: the only entity selectable was a
direct neighbour of the source class.

`CohortLink` now carries an ordered `path: List[CohortHop]` that the
engine walks from the surviving members. Hop 0's source is the rule's
class (locked), hop *i*'s source is hop *i-1*'s `target_class`, and the
last hop's `target_class` is the "shared entity" two members must
reach to be considered linked. Single-hop rules — the old form — are
auto-promoted to a 1-hop path so every existing rule keeps working
unchanged; the engine never sees the legacy fields directly.

Algorithm: a uniform path-walker over the in-memory triple set. The
edge build now does a single forward expansion per hop, accumulating
`{terminal_uri -> {source_members}}`, and only at the terminal does it
emit pairwise edges. For 1-hop links this is the same number of
operations as before; for N-hop it's O(|members| × Σ|out_deg|) over
the path, dominated by hop 0 in practice.

UI: each link row is now a *path card* with one hop per line. Each
hop renders a locked source pill (the rule's class for hop 0,
hop *i-1*'s target otherwise), a `via` predicate dropdown, and a
`target_class` dropdown — both filtered by the
domain/range-aware dependent rule already in place from the previous
release. "Add hop" appends a hop, the "+" on a hop's right removes it
(except hop 0, which is required). The terminal hop carries a
`shared` badge so the meaning of the path is unambiguous. Editing a
hop propagates downstream: the next hop's source pill updates and its
dropdowns re-filter live. A new starter template,
*Multi-hop linkage*, seeds a fresh 2-hop path.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/graph_analysis/models.py
   - New `CohortHop(via, target_class)` dataclass with `to_dict` /
     `from_dict` round-trip + whitespace stripping.
   - `CohortLink` gains `path: List[CohortHop]` and exposes `hops()`
     (auto-promotes legacy `shared_class`+`via` to a 1-hop path) and
     `terminal_class` (last hop's target). Legacy fields are kept on
     the dataclass and round-tripped through `to_dict` / `from_dict`,
     so older saved rules deserialise into a working `CohortLink`.
   - `CohortRule.validate()` walks `lk.hops()` per link and emits a
     per-hop error when `via` or `target_class` is missing.

2. src/back/core/graph_analysis/__init__.py
   - Re-exports `CohortHop` so callers can import it from the package
     root.

3. src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortBuilder.py
