## Cohort engine — restore lenient type filter on path hops

Context: User reported the cohort designer returning *"0 cohorts, 0 of
6 members grouped, 0 edges, 0 ms"* on a perfectly reasonable rule
shortly after the multi-hop refactor. Reproduced with a
6-Person / 3-Project graph that had `:assignedTo` triples but no
`rdf:type` triples for `:Project`. The pre-multi-hop engine produced 5
edges + 2 cohorts on this same graph; the new engine produced zero.

Root cause: the path-walker enforces `nbr in type_index[h.target_class]`
when `target_class` is set. Previously, the legacy edge builder used
`type_index.get(...) or None` — so an *empty* type set (no
`rdf:type` triples at all for the target class) was coerced to `None`
and the type filter was disabled. The multi-hop refactor kept the
empty-set semantics, which silently filtered out every neighbour and
yielded zero edges on graphs that don't materialise types
(R2RML output without explicit type triples, CSV-loaded data,
W3C-imported graphs that rely on `rdfs:domain` for typing).

Fix: in `_walk_path`, treat an empty `type_index[target_class]` as
"no filter" (`allowed = None`), matching the legacy semantics. The
strict filter still applies whenever the type set is non-empty — so
the *typed* multi-hop scenario (`Person → Project → ComplianceType`
with full `rdf:type` triples) still drops walks whose intermediate
node isn't an instance of the declared class.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortBuilder.py
   - `_walk_path`: `allowed = type_index.get(h.target_class) or None`
     (empty / missing entry → no filter), with an in-line docstring
     explaining the lenient fallback and when it kicks in.

2. tests/test_cohort_builder.py
   - New `TestMultiHopPath.test_target_class_with_no_rdf_type_triples_is_lenient`
     reproducing the user's scenario: 6 Persons + assignedTo to 3
     Projects, no `rdf:type` for Project. Asserts 5 edges + 2 cohorts
     (clique-of-3 bridged by Bob into {Alice, Bob, Carol, Frank}, plus
     {Dave, Eve}). This test is RED on pre-fix code (0 edges, 0
     cohorts) and GREEN after the fix.

The strictly-typed path test
(`test_path_target_class_filters_intermediate_node`) still passes:
the multi-hop graph has `rdf:type ComplianceType` triples for
CT-Exempt / CT-Standard, so the type set is non-empty and the strict
filter is honoured.

