## Cohort discovery — per-hop `where` filters on multi-hop linkage paths

Context

Even after the lenient-type fallback fix (above), users who had the
*correct* multi-hop path (`Person → Project → ComplianceType`) but
attached the descriptive constraint to rule-level compatibility
(`value_equals(complianceTypeId = "Individual")`) still saw "0
cohorts, 0 of N members grouped, 0 edges".

Root cause: `complianceTypeId` is a property of `ComplianceType`, not
`Person`. The compatibility section applies node filters to the
*source class* — by Stage 3a every Person was dropped (no value for
`:complianceTypeId`), so Stage 3b had nothing to walk. The path
itself was fine; the constraint was just attached to the wrong class.

Fix: introduce a per-hop `where` filter so users can constrain the
hop's *target* node directly — *"… → ComplianceType where
complianceTypeId = 'Individual'"*. Reuses the existing
`value_equals` / `value_in` / `value_range` primitives;
`same_value` is rejected at validation time (it's a pairwise edge
constraint, meaningless on a single node).

Changes

1. src/back/core/graph_analysis/models.py
   - `CohortHop` gains an optional `where: List[CohortCompat]` field
     (defaults to empty list, omitted from `to_dict()` when empty so
     existing JSON payloads round-trip unchanged).
   - `CohortHop.from_dict` decodes the `where` array.
   - `CohortRule.validate()` walks each hop's `where` and emits the
     same per-primitive errors as rule-level compatibility; rejects
     `same_value` at hop scope.

2. src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortBuilder.py
   - New `_hop_where_attr_index(triples, links)` builds a
     `predicate -> {subject: value}` map over the union of hop-where
     properties. Unlike `_fetch_attrs_for_props`, it does NOT
     restrict to the rule's source-class members — hop targets sit
     mid-path and are instances of the hop's `target_class`.
   - `_walk_path` accepts the hop-attr index and, after the
     `target_class` check, rejects neighbours whose where filters
     don't pass.
   - New module-level `_hop_where_passes(where, node, hop_attrs)`
     mirrors `_node_filter_passes` semantics (`allow_missing`
     honoured; `same_value` silently skipped per validation).

3. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - `_normalizeLink` ensures every hop has a `where: []` array.
   - New `addHopWhere(linkIdx, hopIdx, type)` /
     `removeHopWhere(linkIdx, hopIdx, whereIdx)`.
   - `_renderHopRow` now wraps the hop in a `cohort-hop-wrap` so a
