## Cohort discovery — tree-style multi-hop path renderer

Context

The previous path UI laid each hop out horizontally as a row:
``[Source] → [via select] → [Target select] [shared] [where 2] [×]``.
With a 2-hop or 3-hop chain it became hard to read the direction of
the path at a glance — the source class was repeated on every row,
the where pane lived to the right, and there was no visual cue that
hops are sequential rather than parallel.

Fix

1. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js — ``_renderLinkCard``
   and ``_renderHopRow`` rewritten to emit a vertical tree:
     - Path opens with a single root node showing the rule's
       ``class_uri`` chip with a "source" hint.
     - Each hop renders two stacked rows: a ``via`` edge with the
       predicate select and a down-arrow, then the target node
       (chip-styled select with bullet, badges, and remove button).
     - The terminal hop swaps the bullet circle for a flag icon
       (``bi-flag-fill``), uses a green chip variant and masks the
       parent vertical line below it so the path visually
       "terminates".
     - Where panes nest naturally under their target node, indented
       to the right of the bullet.

2. src/front/static/query/css/query-cohorts.css
     - New ``.cohort-tree``, ``.cohort-tree-root``, ``.cohort-tree-hops``,
       ``.cohort-tree-hop``, ``.cohort-tree-edge``, ``.cohort-tree-node``,
       ``.cohort-tree-bullet``, ``.cohort-class-chip``,
       ``.cohort-class-chip-root``, ``.cohort-class-chip-terminal``,
       and ``.cohort-class-chip-select`` rules.
     - Vertical line drawn via dashed ``border-left`` on
       ``.cohort-tree-hops``; horizontal hop connectors drawn via
       dashed ``::before`` on each ``.cohort-tree-hop``; terminal
       node masks the line below itself with ``::after`` painted in
       the body background.
     - Target ``select`` styled to look like a chip (custom CSS-only
       caret arrow, no native ``border``) so the chosen class reads
       as a visual destination rather than a form input.
     - Removed obsolete ``.cohort-hop-list``, ``.cohort-hop``,
       ``.cohort-hop-source``, ``.cohort-hop-arrow``, and
       ``.cohort-hop-wrap`` rules — no remaining references in
