## Cohort discovery — preview members show URI, ID, and Label

Context

The dry-run preview rendered each cohort member as a single line
showing only the URI's local name (``_localName(m)``). For typed
URIs like ``Person/2`` that meant the user only saw ``2`` — no
human-readable label, no domain identifier (``Person/2``), no
copyable URI. Useless when the population is anonymous (just IDs)
and the rdfs:label data is right there in the graph.

Fix

1. src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py
   - ``dry_run_cohort`` now post-processes the ``CohortResult``
     payload through new ``_enrich_cohort_members`` helper before
     returning. It collects the union of all member URIs, makes a
     single ``store.get_entity_metadata`` call, and rewrites
     ``cohorts[*].members`` from ``List[str]`` to a
     ``List[{uri, id, label}]``.
   - ``id`` is the local segment after the last ``/`` or ``#`` —
     what humans read as the entity's domain identifier (e.g.
     ``Person/2`` URI → id ``2``). When the URI has no separator,
     ``id`` falls back to the URI itself.
   - ``label`` is best-effort. Missing labels degrade to ``""``;
     the UI then renders the id as the headline.
   - Errors during the metadata fetch are swallowed (logged at
     debug) and the original URI strings are preserved — the
     preview must not crash on store hiccups.

2. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - New ``_renderCohortMember(m)`` renders one member as a small
     card: bold label (or id fallback) on top with a chip showing
     the id, and the full URI underneath in a click-to-copy
     ``<code>`` element. Backwards compatible with the legacy
     plain-string member shape — degrades gracefully when the
     enrichment step fails.
   - ``_renderPreviewBody`` now wires a clipboard handler on every
     ``[data-copy]`` URI element with a "copied ✓" flash.

3. src/front/static/query/css/query-cohorts.css
   - New ``.cohort-preview-member``, ``-headline``, ``-label``,
     ``-id``, ``-uri`` rules for the three-row layout. The URI line
     is small / muted by default and turns primary on hover, success
     after a successful copy.

4. tests/test_dtwin_cohort.py
   - Three new tests in ``TestDryRunAndMaterialize``:
     - ``test_dry_run_enriches_members_with_id_and_label`` — happy
       path, asserts each member is a dict with the three keys and
       the right label.
     - ``test_dry_run_falls_back_to_empty_label_when_metadata_missing``
       — labels missing → empty strings, dict shape preserved.
     - ``test_dry_run_survives_metadata_fetch_failure`` — store
       error during enrichment leaves the original URI strings
       intact so the engine result still surfaces.

