============================================================
Cohort Discovery — connect the trunk to the parent bullet
============================================================

Context

After the previous tree fix the dashed trunk indented under the
correct parent, but it still didn't *touch* the bullet — the
children container's ``border-left`` started below the parent's
where pane (or below the chip when there was no where pane), so
visually:

  ○ Project  [×]
  ┊ where: hasStatus = "Active"
  ┊
  ┊                            ← trunk starts here, ~2rem too low
  └─ via hasComplianceType ↓
     ⚑ ComplianceType

We need the trunk to actually originate from the Project bullet.
Pure CSS can't compute the offset because the where pane height
is dynamic (number of filter rows + wrap), so we measure it.

Fix

1. src/front/static/query/css/query-cohorts.css
   - Combined ``.cohort-tree-hops-root::before`` and
     ``.cohort-tree-hops-children::before`` into a single rule:
     a dashed vertical extension positioned absolutely with
     ``top: calc(0px - var(--cohort-trunk-up))`` and
     ``height: var(--cohort-trunk-up)``. The variable is set by
     JS at render time from the actually-measured offsets.
   - ``.cohort-tree-hop::before`` (the horizontal connector) and
     ``.cohort-tree-hop-terminal::after`` (the trunk-end mask)
     now use ``top: var(--cohort-bullet-y, 3rem)`` so they land
     exactly on the bullet rather than on the via row above it.
     Connector ``width`` widened from ``0.85rem`` to ``1.35rem``
     so it reaches the bullet center.
   - Terminal mask widened (``left: -1.2rem; width: 0.5rem``) to
     fully cover the 2px trunk regardless of sub-pixel rounding.
   - Removed the now-unused ``margin-top: -0.4rem; padding-top:
     0.5rem`` hack on ``.cohort-tree-hops-children``.

2. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - New ``_relayoutCohortTrunks(root)`` helper. After every
     ``_renderLinks()``, the next animation frame measures:
       a) each ``.cohort-tree-hop`` bullet's y-offset from the
          hop's top → ``--cohort-bullet-y`` (drives ::before
          connector + ::after terminal mask),
       b) the gap between every ``.cohort-tree-root``'s bullet
          and its sibling ``.cohort-tree-hops-root`` →
          ``--cohort-trunk-up`` on the hops-root,
       c) the gap between every ``.cohort-tree-hops-children``'s
          top and its parent hop's bullet →
          ``--cohort-trunk-up`` on the children container.
     CSS uses these variables to draw the missing ``::before``
     extension straight from the bullet to the existing trunk.

Result

  ○ Project  [×]
  │  where: hasStatus = "Active"
  │
  │                              ← trunk now starts at Project
  └─ via hasComplianceType ↓
     ⚑ ComplianceType  shared

Even with multiple where filters or no where filters at all,
the trunk's start point tracks the bullet exactly because the
extension height is measured per-hop.

