============================================================
Cohort Discovery — drop the white "trunk-mask" stripe
============================================================

Context

The terminal hop's ``::after`` pseudo painted ``--bs-body-bg``
(``#fff``) over the trunk past the flag to fake a path-end.
But ``.cohort-link-card`` sits on ``rgba(0,0,0,0.02)``, so the
mask read as a *brighter* white stripe running from the flag
to the bottom of the card — exactly what we tried to hide.

Fix

The right way to "stop" the trunk is to not draw it past the
bullet in the first place — kill the mask, draw the trunk as
a measured ``::before`` pseudo with a precise height instead
of a fixed ``border-left``.

1. src/front/static/query/css/query-cohorts.css
   - Removed ``border-left`` from ``.cohort-tree-hops:not(:empty)``
     and the ``.cohort-tree-hop-terminal::after`` mask entirely.
   - ``.cohort-tree-hops:not(:empty)::before`` now draws the full
     trunk for that nesting level, with both ``--cohort-trunk-up``
     (extension above the container to reach the parent bullet)
     and ``--cohort-trunk-height`` (total height ending exactly
     at the first child hop's bullet centre) set by JS.
   - Added ``pointer-events: none`` on the trunk pseudo so it
     never swallows clicks on the chips it sits behind.

2. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - ``_relayoutCohortTrunks`` factored its per-container logic
     into a single ``setTrunkVars(hops, parentBullet)`` helper
     that measures both ``up`` (gap parent-bullet → container
     top, clamped at 0) and ``height`` (parent-bullet → first
     child bullet). Result: the trunk lands precisely on each
     bullet at every nesting level, and there is no overshoot.
   - Same helper drives the root level (``.cohort-tree-root`` →
     ``.cohort-tree-hops-root``) and every nested level
     (``.cohort-tree-hop`` → ``.cohort-tree-hops-children``).

Result

  ●─── Person  source
  │
  └─── via PhasProject ↓
       ○─── Project  [×]
       │     where: hasStatus = "Active"
       │
       └─── via hasComplianceType ↓
            ⚑ ComplianceType  shared        ← path ends here,
                                              no white stripe
                                              continues below

Files modified
  - src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
  - src/front/static/query/css/query-cohorts.css

Tests
  - Full suite: 1977 / 1977 passed.
  - Manual: 1- / 2- / 3-hop paths render with the trunk ending
    cleanly at the terminal flag, no bright stripe below it
    regardless of where-pane height or card background.

