## Frontend Design System rule — sidebar, breadcrumb, section actions, message bus

Context: Third pass on the rule file, requested by the user, to make
four high-impact UI invariants explicit:
(1) sidebar behaviour (collapse, URL sync, public API, do-not patterns),
(2) breadcrumb behaviour and style,
(3) action buttons must live in the section's top-right header,
(4) all user-facing messages must route through the navbar
Notification Center. Each rule is grounded in code I read in this
pass: `global/js/sidebar-nav.js`, `global/js/breadcrumb.js`,
`global/css/sidebar-layout.css`, `global/css/components.css`,
`global/js/utils.js`, plus the canonical `.section-header
d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center` pattern used by
~15 partials (e.g. `_ontology_entities.html`, `_registry_domains.html`).

Changes:

1. .cursor/11-frontend-design.mdc
   - New "Sidebar Behaviour" section. Documents the auto-init
     contract from `sidebar-nav.js` (`data-section` ↔ `<id>-section`
     pairing, exactly one `.active`); state, history and keyboard
     (URL `?section=` sync, popstate restore, `localStorage` key
     `ontobricks-sidebar-collapsed`, default-collapsed); the
     `sidebarSectionChanged` event as the official extension point;
     the public API table (`switchTo`, `getActiveSection`,
     `toggleCollapse`, `init` with `onSectionChange` /
     `onBeforeSectionChange` veto); style rules (200/48 px width,
     0.82rem nav-link, left-border accent, greyscale active state,
     uppercase 0.65rem `.sidebar-title`, badge auto-wrapping);
     disabled gates (`.sidebar-disabled`,
     `.sidebar-requires-domain`, `.sync-requires-ready`,
     `.view-mode-hidden`); and an explicit don'ts list (no
     hand-coded nav, no per-link click handlers, no
     `style.display`, no per-page localStorage, no manual
     `--ob-chrome-height`).
   - New "Breadcrumb Behaviour & Style" section. Documents the
     URL-derived crumbs from `breadcrumb.js` (`_ROUTE_MAP` /
     `_HIERARCHY` Registry → Domain → Ontology → Mapping → Digital
     Twin); the live "active section" crumb driven by
     `sidebarSectionChanged`; that the Domain label is read from
     `#currentDomainName` (no extra fetch); that breadcrumb.js owns
     `--ob-chrome-height`; the `.ob-breadcrumb` style contract
     (light bg, bottom border, 0.8rem, bootstrap-icons `\F285`
     chevron separator, `--bs-secondary` link colour, active crumb
     in body colour weight 500); and the don'ts (no per-page
     breadcrumbs, no manual `#obBreadcrumbList` mutation, no
     separator changes, no forcing visible on single-crumb pages).
   - New "Section Header & Top-Right Actions" section. Defines the
     canonical skeleton `.section-header d-flex
     justify-content-between align-items-center mb-4` with title
     block on the left and action buttons on the right; the
     mandatory order (icon-only utility group → secondary CTA →
     primary CTA, rightmost = most important); use of `btn-sm`;
     mandatory `title=` on icon-only buttons; that `<h4>` is the
     section title level (page-level `<h1>` belongs to
     `.page-header` on standalone pages); and the anti-patterns
     (no floating FABs, no buttons in `.card-header`, no full-size
     buttons, no buttons below the data, no primary CTA on the
     left).
   - Strengthened "Popups, Modals, Confirmations & Notifications"
     with two non-negotiable rules at the top: (a) no native
     popups, (b) all messages route through the navbar Notification
     Center. Added a "Single message bus — the navbar Notification
     Center" subsection describing the `#notifCenterDropdown`
     infrastructure (toggle, dropdown, badge, ring buffer cap,
     time-ago labels, mark-read on open). Added a "What goes
     through the Notification Center" routing table mapping each
     message source (API result, validation, background task,
     destructive confirmation, free-text input, long-form preview)
     to the right helper.
   - Extended the "What NOT to Do" anti-pattern list with: per-page
     toast/alert/status `<div>`, `console.error` as sole error
     signal, sidebar style.display toggling, page-code writes to
     `--ob-chrome-height`, custom per-page breadcrumbs, action
     buttons outside `.section-header`, hand-coded sidebar items,
     per-link click handlers on the sidebar.

