================================================================================
Title: Cohort Discovery — route Save/Delete through the navbar Notification Center
================================================================================

Context
-------
The cohort `save()` / `deleteRule()` flows surfaced their result via the
inline `#cohortStatus` rail line ("Saved …", "Save failed", etc.). Every
other save action in the app routes through the navbar Notification Center
via `showNotification` (mapping save, domain save, business-rules save,
settings save…), with a transient toast for non-info types. The cohort
flow now matches that convention.

Changes
-------
1. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - `save()`: validation, HTTP failure, network failure and success now
     all call a new `_notify(message, type)` helper instead of the inline
     `_setStatus`. Types are aligned with the rest of the codebase
     (`'success' | 'error' | 'warning' | 'info'`). Inline rail is
     cleared on entry so stale "Unsaved changes…" doesn't linger.
   - `deleteRule()`: same change — success and failure go through
     `_notify` (`'Cohort rule deleted'` / `'Delete failed'`).
   - New `_notify()` thin wrapper: prefers `window.showNotification` (the
     standard helper from `global/js/utils.js`) and falls back to
     `console` if it's not loaded yet, so messages are never silently
     dropped during early init.
   - In-memory states (Drafting…, Computing preview…, Outputs configured…,
     Unsaved changes…) keep using `_setStatus` — they're transient
     progress hints, not save outcomes.

