================================================================================
Title: Cohort Discovery (Ontology) — fix unscrollable Build form
================================================================================

Context
-------
On Ontology > Advanced > Cohorts, the Build-rule tab content (Identity,
What, Linked-when, Compatibility, Group type — five vertically stacked
sections) was getting clipped at the bottom of the viewport with no
way to scroll. Reproduced on a small laptop window: section 5 (Group
type tiles + Min size) sat below the fold, mouse wheel did nothing,
and the page-level sidebar-content scrollbar didn't appear either.

Root cause: `.sidebar-section.active` is `display: flex; flex-direction:
column; height: 100%` and `.sidebar-section > .content-section` is
`flex: 1; min-height: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column`, so
the cohort partial's `.content-section` is height-capped to the
viewport. The other ontology partials work around this because they
nest a `.card` or `.ob-tab-content` directly under `.content-section`
— `sidebar-layout.css` has explicit `overflow-y: auto` rules for
those. The cohort design partial uses a CSS Grid (`.cohort-layout`)
as the direct child of `.content-section`, which has no overflow
rule of its own, so its content overflows the flex-constrained
parent without producing a scrollbar.

The Digital Twin run page uses the same `.cohort-layout` grid and
benefits from the same fix.

Fix
---
1. src/front/static/query/css/query-cohorts.css
   - `.cohort-layout` now declares `flex: 1; min-height: 0;
     overflow-y: auto; overflow-x: hidden;`. Combined with the
     existing flex-column `.content-section` parent, the grid now
     fills the remaining vertical space and produces its own
     vertical scrollbar when content exceeds it. `.cohort-rail-body`
     keeps its independent `max-height: 50vh` scroll for the saved
     rules list — both scroll regions coexist cleanly.
   - The mobile breakpoint (`@media (max-width: 992px)`) is
     unchanged: it already collapses the grid to a single column,
     and the new flex/overflow rules apply uniformly so the same
     scroll behaviour kicks in on narrow screens.

Files modified
  - src/front/static/query/css/query-cohorts.css
  - changelogs/v0.3.0/2026-05-04.log

