## Cohort code review — structural follow-ups (V1, V2, D3)

Context: After the safe-batch cleanup (D1, DC1–DC5, V3, V4), the
remaining structural items from the cohort code review were applied
in three Fowler-style refactors. Behaviour preserved end-to-end —
all 2023 tests still pass.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortVocabulary.py (NEW)
   - **V1 / Extract Class**: created `CohortVocabulary` (one public
     class, PascalCase filename) that owns every cohort-related URI
     fragment (`Cohort`, `inCohort`, `fromRule`, `cohortSize`,
     `cohort` path) plus six builders (`cohort_class`, `in_cohort`,
     `from_rule`, `cohort_size`, `cohort_prefix`, `cohort`). The
     base `join(base, fragment)` helper centralises the `/` vs `#`
     separator convention used elsewhere in the codebase.

2. src/back/core/graph_analysis/__init__.py
   - **V1 / Move Function** + thin BC wrappers per `.cursor/07
     §__init__.py Conventions`: stripped the six top-level helpers
     that previously held business logic. They now delegate to
     `CohortVocabulary` and remain exported under their original
     names (`cohort_class_uri`, `in_cohort_predicate`,
     `from_rule_predicate`, `cohort_size_predicate`,
     `cohort_uri_prefix`, `cohort_uri`) so external callers and
     existing tests keep working. `CohortVocabulary` and the
     fragment constants are also re-exported.

3. src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortBuilder.py
   - Replaced the six bulk imports with a single
     `from back.core.graph_analysis.CohortVocabulary import
     CohortVocabulary` and rewrote the four call sites to use
     `CohortVocabulary.cohort_class / from_rule / cohort_size /
     in_cohort / cohort_prefix / cohort` -- shorter, more
     discoverable, single source of truth.

4. src/back/objects/digitaltwin/CohortService.py (NEW)
   - **V2 / Extract Class**: lifted the entire cohort block (~520
     LOC) out of `DigitalTwin.py` into a focused
     :class:`CohortService` with renamed methods (`list_rules`,
     `save_rule`, `delete_rule`, `dry_run`, `materialize`,
     `class_stats`, `edge_count`, `node_count`, `path_trace`,
     `sample_values`, `explain`, `suggest_uc_target`,
     `probe_uc_write`). The redundant `cohort_` prefix is dropped
     from the internal API; the public/legacy names live on
     `DigitalTwin` (see #5). Constructor takes a `DomainSession`,
     matching the rest of `back/objects/digitaltwin/`. Helpers
     (`_builder`, `_result_to_dict`, `_enrich_members`) become
     instance / static methods on this class.

5. src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py
   - **V2 / Replace Method with Method Object**: replaced the 460
     LOC cohort block with 13 thin delegating wrappers (e.g.
     `def list_cohort_rules(self): return
     self._cohort_service().list_rules()`). The wrappers preserve
     every previously-exposed name and signature, so routes that
     called `DigitalTwin(domain).cohort_*` (and
     `DigitalTwin.cohort_probe_uc_write`) keep working without
     changes -- handy for any consumer outside this PR.

6. src/back/objects/digitaltwin/__init__.py
   - **V2**: re-exported `CohortService` so consumers can write
     `from back.objects.digitaltwin import CohortService` (the
     internal API now uses this directly -- see #7).

7. src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py
   - **D3 / Introduce Parameter Object** + **Replace Function with
     Command via FastAPI Depends**: added a `CohortEngineContext`
     dataclass (domain, settings, store, graph_name, service) and a
     `cohort_engine_context` FastAPI dependency that builds it once,
     plus a tiny `cohort_json_body` dep that centralises the
