## ob-tabs — bake white background + cohort-page padding into the class

Context: After standardising the underline tab style, the visual
"finish" still differed across pages because each template
re-applied padding (`px-3 pt-2` on Cohorts, `px-3 pt-3` on DQ /
Business Rules / Axioms / DT-DataQuality / DT-Inference) and the
white tab strip only appeared when the tabs sat inside a `.card`.
The user picked the **Ontology > Cohorts** tab strip — white
background, `px-3 pt-2` padding, 2px primary underline — as the
single reference and asked us to bake it into the contract.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/global/css/components.css
   - `.nav-tabs.ob-tabs` now sets `background: #fff` and
     `padding: 0.5rem 1rem 0` (the `px-3 pt-2` equivalent) by
     default. The strip looks like the Cohorts header out of the
     box, regardless of whether it is wrapped in a `.card`,
     `.card-body p-0`, or sits directly in a section.
   - The CSS comment block was rewritten to call out the new
     contract (white bg + baked padding + "do not re-apply
     `px-3 pt-2` / `px-3 pt-3`").

2. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_cohorts.html
   - Dropped redundant `px-3 pt-2` from the tab `<ul>`.

3. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_dataquality.html
   - Dropped `px-3 pt-3` (now baked in as `pt-2`-equivalent).

4. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_business_rules.html
   - Same: `px-3 pt-3` removed.

5. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_axioms.html
   - Same: `px-3 pt-3` removed.

6. src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_dataquality.html
   - Same: `px-3 pt-3` removed; `flex-shrink-0` kept (still
     needed inside the flex card body).

7. src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_reasoning.html
   - Same as above.

8. .cursor/11-frontend-design.mdc
   - *Tabs (`.ob-tabs`) — flat-underline style* section updated
     to:
     * call out the Ontology > Cohorts page as the canonical
       reference,
     * document the baked-in white background and padding,
     * trim the catalogued combinations (`px-3 pt-3` is gone;
       the active list is `mb-0`, `nav-fill small`, and
       `nav-fill small flex-shrink-0`),
     * add a new rule "do not re-apply spacing utilities on the
       tab `<ul>` — the padding is already baked in",
     * extend the anti-patterns list with the same point.

