─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Section: ob-tabs head — rounded corners + grey outline + full-page fill
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Context
  Follow-up on the ob-tabs visual contract. User feedback:
    1. The tab "head" should look like the Ontology > Information
       card-header — rounded corners and a grey outline, **not**
       a flat strip flush against a card border.
    2. Tabs + body together should fill the page from below the
       section header to the bottom of the viewport, exactly like
       the single card on Ontology > Information (no short
       free-floating cards leaving white space underneath).
  Both bullets needed to apply globally to every page that uses
  `ob-tabs`, while keeping the existing baked-in background /
  padding contract intact.

Changes
  1. `src/front/static/global/css/components.css`
     - Promoted `.nav-tabs.ob-tabs` from a flat strip to a
       card-header look:
         * `border: 1px solid var(--db-border)` on top / left /
           right (the "grey line"),
         * `border-bottom-width: 2px` for the underline (grey
           baseline that turns primary under the active tab),
         * `border-top-left-radius` / `border-top-right-radius`
           = `var(--bs-card-border-radius, 0.375rem)` for the
           rounded angles,
         * bottom corners explicitly squared so the strip mates
           cleanly with the body below.
     - Added a parent-aware "drop the outer border when nested"
       block: `.card-body > .nav-tabs.ob-tabs`,
       `.card-header > .nav-tabs.ob-tabs`,
       `.card > .nav-tabs.ob-tabs` strip the new top / left /
       right borders + radius so the strip doesn't double-border
       the outer card (cohorts / dq / business-rules / axioms
       still look correct).
     - Generalised the adjacent-sibling rule from
       `.nav-tabs.ob-tabs + .card` to also cover
       `+ .ob-tab-content` and `+ .tab-content`, with
       `border-top-left-radius / border-top-right-radius: 0
       !important` so the body's top corners square up to meet
       the strip.
     - Added a new `ob-tabs-wrap` flex-column utility for the
       full-height pattern. When dropped as a direct child of
       `.content-section`, it grows to fill (`flex: 1`,
       `min-height: 0`, `overflow: hidden`); inside, the strip
       gets `flex-shrink: 0` and the body
       (`.tab-content` / `.ob-tab-content` / `.card`) gets
       `flex: 1 + overflow-y: auto`. Available for templates
       that need the fill behaviour deeper in the markup.
  2. `src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_information.html`
     - Dropped the now-redundant `border-top-0 rounded-top-0`
       utility classes from the `<div class="card">` that
       follows the tabs — the adjacent-sibling rule handles this
       with `!important`.
  3. `src/front/templates/settings.html`
     - Same cleanup: removed `border-top-0 rounded-top-0` from
       the settings tab body card.
  4. `.cursor/11-frontend-design.mdc`
     - Rewrote the "Tabs (`ob-tabs`)" section to describe the new
       card-header look: rounded top corners, grey outline,
       parent-aware nested behaviour, generalised adjacent-sibling
       rule (cards + ob-tab-content + tab-content all get their
       top border + corners neutralised).
     - Added a new "Full-height pattern" rule with two recipes:
         (a) place tabs + body as direct children of
             `.content-section` (relies on existing
             `sidebar-layout.css` flex chain),
         (b) wrap them in `<div class="ob-tabs-wrap">` when (a)
             is not available.
     - Extended the anti-patterns list:
         * "do not re-apply `border-top-0 rounded-top-0` on the
           card after `ob-tabs`" (the rule handles it),
         * "no short, free-floating tabs-cards that don't reach
           the bottom — use the full-height pattern".

